Parameter: WSpt – Use this VAR to set active power setpoint when ICON(M) is set to 0
VarSpt – Use this VAR to set reactive power setpoint when ICON(M) is set to 0
FrqSpt - Use this VAR to set frequency setpoint
VolSpt - Use this VAR to set voltage setpoint
TmpStk – Use this VAR to set the temperature of stack – Default is 119 degrees
Xpu – X part of impedance for current injection – should be equal to X for gen. in LF
Rpu - R part of impedance for current injection – should be equal to R for gen. in LF
SetpointChangeFlag – Flag to detect setpoint change when ICON(M) is set to 0
Vth_r – real part of thevenin voltage applied in the current injection routine
Vth_i – imaginary part of thevenin voltage applied in the current injection routine
FRTDetect – Flag to Check whether FRT is enabled or not
VI_X – reactive part of Virtual impedance when in FRT
VI_R – real part of Virtual impedance when in FRT
VCtlHi1Lim_Out – Flag to check whether High Voltage Protection 1 is activated
VCtlHi2Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Voltage Protection 2 is activated
VCtlHi3Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Voltage Protection 3 is activated
VCtlHi4Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Voltage Protection 4 is activated
VCtlHi5Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Voltage Protection 5 is activated
VCtlHi6Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Voltage Protection 6 is activated
VCtlLo1Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Voltage Protection 1 is activated
VCtlLo2Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Voltage Protection 2 is activated
VCtlLo3Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Voltage Protection 3 is activated
VCtlLo4Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Voltage Protection 4 is activated
VCtlLo5Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Voltage Protection 5 is activated
VCtlLo6Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Voltage Protection 6 is activated
HzCtlHi1Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Frequency Protection 1 is activated
HzCtlHi2Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Frequency Protection 2 is activated
HzCtlHi3Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Frequency Protection 3 is activated
HzCtlHi4Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Frequency Protection 4 is activated
HzCtlHi5Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Frequency Protection 5 is activated
HzCtlHi6Lim_Out - Flag to check whether High Frequency Protection 6 is activated
HzCtlLo1Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Frequency Protection 1 is activated
HzCtlLo2Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Frequency Protection 2 is activated
HzCtlLo3Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Frequency Protection 3 is activated
HzCtlLo4Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Frequency Protection 4 is activated
HzCtlLo5Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Frequency Protection 5 is activated
HzCtlLo6Lim_Out - Flag to check whether Low Frequency Protection 6 is activated
